&gt;&gt;Kristi Yamaguchi: Thank you.

00:25:56.140 --> 00:26:01.110
&gt;&gt;FEMALE #1: I'm wondering if you got nervous
before you competed and what you did to try

00:26:01.110 --> 00:26:02.110
to control that.

00:26:02.110 --> 00:26:03.150
&gt;&gt;Kristi Yamaguchi: OK.

00:26:03.150 --> 00:26:04.990
Can you hear me still?

00:26:04.990 --> 00:26:06.260
Is this still on?

00:26:06.260 --> 00:26:07.669
&gt;&gt;Female Presenter: Yeah.

00:26:07.669 --> 00:26:08.669
OK.

00:26:08.669 --> 00:26:14.290
&gt;&gt;Kristi Yamaguchi: Definitely got nervous
every time I competed, even for every show,

00:26:14.290 --> 00:26:16.210
almost every performance.

00:26:16.210 --> 00:26:21.950
But I think just a lot of positive reinforcement.

00:26:21.950 --> 00:26:23.740
The night before the competition,

00:26:23.740 --> 00:26:30.840
I did a lot of imagery and walking through
what I wanted to do and going through the

00:26:30.840 --> 00:26:33.770
entire routine, making sure it's perfect.

00:26:33.770 --> 00:26:38.660
[giggles] If it wasn't, I'd go back and rewind
and do it until it was how I wanted and then

00:26:38.660 --> 00:26:40.080
I could fall asleep.

00:26:40.080 --> 00:26:45.980
But especially, right before stepping on the
ice, there's a lot of anxiety and it was just

00:26:45.980 --> 00:26:53.580
common breathing techniques as well as telling
myself, "I've trained for this.

00:26:53.580 --> 00:26:54.580
I'm ready."

00:26:54.580 --> 00:26:59.620
I think the training that I did leading into
the competitions always was something I leaned

00:26:59.620 --> 00:27:00.620
back on.

00:27:00.620 --> 00:27:06.710
And I said, "I've done this a hundred times
at home, at my rink, in the comfort of my

00:27:06.710 --> 00:27:07.710
surroundings there."

00:27:07.710 --> 00:27:14.260
I just wanted to take myself back to my training
rink and just tell myself it's just like any

00:27:14.260 --> 00:27:15.260
other day.

00:27:15.260 --> 00:27:17.710
"Just go out and do what you can."

00:27:17.710 --> 00:27:24.170
But I think just preparation and the training
helped with the confidence.

00:27:24.170 --> 00:27:25.170
[pause]

