00:27:37.340 --> 00:27:38.980
Thank you very much for coming to Google.

00:27:38.980 --> 00:27:39.980
&gt;&gt;Kristi Yamaguchi: Sure.

00:27:39.980 --> 00:27:43.100
&gt;&gt;FEMALE #2: First of all, I just wanna tell
you that, like Erica said, you've been one

00:27:43.100 --> 00:27:44.260
of my idols growing up.

00:27:44.260 --> 00:27:49.350
There are very few strong Asian American women
in the media to look up to.

00:27:49.350 --> 00:27:52.309
So, thank you for being here and sharing your
story.

00:27:52.309 --> 00:27:57.610
And another question I have is I know that
you grew up in the Bay Area, specifically

00:27:57.610 --> 00:27:59.590
Fremont, which is where I also grew up.

00:27:59.590 --> 00:28:05.659
So, I'd like to hear about how growing up
in the Bay Area in Fremont has influenced

00:28:05.659 --> 00:28:06.659
you.

00:28:06.659 --> 00:28:08.669
&gt;&gt;Kristi Yamaguchi: Yeah.

00:28:08.669 --> 00:28:13.039
I feel like just any other California girl
I guess out there.

00:28:13.039 --> 00:28:19.090
I mean, Fremont was a great place to grow
up in.

00:28:19.090 --> 00:28:26.190
I remember it being very diverse and just
a great place.

00:28:26.190 --> 00:28:33.580
I think being in the Bay Area in general,
I think you have access to so much right at

00:28:33.580 --> 00:28:34.910
your fingertips.

00:28:34.910 --> 00:28:37.590
And I don't know.

00:28:37.590 --> 00:28:44.380
I think my parents were great to support whatever
it was I dreamed of.

00:28:44.380 --> 00:28:53.180
[giggles] People ask, there's been Peggy Fleming,
Brian Boitano, Debbie Thomas, obviously Rudy

00:28:53.180 --> 00:28:57.830
Galindo, and Charlie Tickner, and we're all
from the Bay Area.

00:28:57.830 --> 00:29:03.360
And it's like the Bay Area has produced some
very successful skaters.

00:29:03.360 --> 00:29:06.419
But yet, we've all had different coaches.

00:29:06.419 --> 00:29:08.780
We've all trained at different rinks.

00:29:08.780 --> 00:29:10.000
So, we kinda don't know why.

00:29:10.000 --> 00:29:12.190
I mean, I think we--.

00:29:12.190 --> 00:29:18.460
Skating's popular here and we have a great
set of rinks, but maybe we just have a bigger

00:29:18.460 --> 00:29:20.919
pool of talent to pull from.

00:29:20.919 --> 00:29:27.140
But I can't explain that, but I think it is
a great place as far as nurturing sports and

00:29:27.140 --> 00:29:34.350
being open and allowing different--.

00:29:34.350 --> 00:29:40.260
Skating's probably not the number one sport
to go into, but there's still places to train

00:29:40.260 --> 00:29:41.260
and focus on it.

00:29:41.260 --> 00:29:42.260
&gt;&gt;FEMALE #2: Thank you.

00:29:42.260 --> 00:29:48.780
&gt;&gt;Kristi Yamaguchi: I want this energy.

00:29:48.780 --> 00:29:49.780
[laughter]

00:29:49.780 --> 00:29:51.120
&gt;&gt;FEMALE #3: Hi Kristi.

